Ragnar casts a sideglance at Katya.

Ragnar: Aye, I agree. But you must understand that we Clansmen hold 
tightly to honor. Before we enter your group, you will have to prove 
your worth in battle.

Katya: Therefore, I challenge you, Owlhawk, in a fist fight. The best 
warrior will win, and the loser shall go with the winner.

It was obviously a move that belied the Clanners's will to follow the 
Maximals. Their honor code would not permit them to follow one who has 
not proven himself. Katya was fast, but she seemed to be no match for 
Owlhawk. Still, she was a warrior born, a trueborn. She could still 
win, but it was unlikely.
